data.name: Population Change
data.description: Difference between the population sizes on 1 January of two consecutive years.
data.sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2022). World Population Prospects: The 2022 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

data.name: Rate of population change
data.description: Exponential rate of change of the population over an annual period. It is calculated as ln(P2/P1) where P1 and P2 are the population sizes on 1 January of two consecutive years. It is expressed as a percentage.
data.displayName: Crude rate of total population change
data.sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2022). World Population Prospects: The 2022 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

data.name: Natural change of population
data.description: The difference between the number of live births and the number of deaths during the year. A positive natural change, also known as natural increase, occurs when live births outnumber deaths. A negative natural change, also named as natural decrease, occurs when live births are less numerous than deaths.
data.sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2022). World Population Prospects: The 2022 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

data.name: Crude rate of natural change of population
data.description: The crude rate of natural change is the ratio of the natural change during the year (live births minus deaths) to the average population in that year. The value is expressed per 1 000 persons.
data.displayName: Crude rate of natural change of population
data.sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2022). World Population Prospects: The 2022 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

data.name: Population density
data.description: Number of persons per square Kilometer.
data.sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2022). World Population Prospects: The 2022 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

data.name: Crude birth rate
data.description: Number of live births over a given period divided by the person-years lived by the population over that period.
data.sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2022). World Population Prospects: The 2022 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

data.name: Net Reproduction Rate
data.description: The average number of daughters a hypothetical cohort of women would have at the end of their reproductive period if they were subject during their whole lives to the fertility rates and the mortality rates of a given period. It is expressed as number of daughters per woman.
data.sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2022). World Population Prospects: The 2022 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

data.name: Total births by sex
data.description: Number of live births over a given period.
data.displayName: Total number of live births by sex
data.sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2022). World Population Prospects: The 2022 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

data.name: Sex ratio at birth
data.description: Number of male births per one female birth.
data.displayName: Sex ratio at birth (per female newborn)
data.sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2022). World Population Prospects: The 2022 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

data.name: Crude death rate
data.description: Number of deaths over a given period divided by the person-years lived by the population over that period.
data.sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2022). World Population Prospects: The 2022 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

data.name: Total deaths by sex
data.description: Number of deaths over a given period.
data.sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2022). World Population Prospects: The 2022 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

data.name: Life expectancy at birth
data.description: The average number of years of life expected by a hypothetical cohort of individuals who would be subject throughout their lives to the age-specific mortality rates of a given period.
data.sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2022). World Population Prospects: The 2022 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

data.name: Probability of dying 15-50 (35q15)
data.description: Probability of dying between the fifteen and fiftieth birthdays.
data.displayName: Probability of dying between 15 and 50 (35q15) per 1,000
data.sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2022). World Population Prospects: The 2022 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

data.name: Probability of dying 15-60 (45q15)
data.description: Probability of dying between the fifteen and sixtieth birthdays.
data.displayName: Probability of dying between 15 and 60 (45q15) per 1,000
data.sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2022). World Population Prospects: The 2022 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

data.name: Deaths by 5-year age groups and sex
data.description: Number of deaths by age groups and by sex over a given period.
data.displayName: Deaths by age and sex - abridged
data.sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2022). World Population Prospects: The 2022 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

data.name: Total net-migration
data.description: Net number of migrants, that is, the number of immigrants minus the number of emigrants.
data.sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2022). World Population Prospects: The 2022 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

data.name: Crude rate of net migration
data.description: The crude rate of net migration is defined as the ratio of net migration during the year to the average population in that year. The value is expressed per 1000 persons.
data.sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2022). World Population Prospects: The 2022 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

data.name: Median age of population
data.description: Age that divides the population in two parts of equal size, that is, there are as many persons with ages above the median as there are with ages below the median. It is expressed as years.
data.displayName: Median age of the total population
data.sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2022). World Population Prospects: The 2022 Revision, custom data acquired via website.

data.name: Fertility rates by age of mother (1-year)
data.description: Number of live births to women at a particular age, divided by the number of women (i.e., person-years) at that age over a given period.
data.displayName: Fertility rates by age of mother (1-year)
data.downloadFileName: Age-specific fertility rates by age of mother
data.sourceCitation: United Nations, Department of Economic and Social Affairs, Population Division (2022). World Population Prospects: The 2022 Revision, custom data acquired via website.
